text:
Hi There, 
I have NodeSDK set up. And i notice that even after bootstrapping the file 
/var/hyperledger/production/.membersrvc/tlsca.cert is not getting generated for me.. I am following the hyper ledger documentation for the set up.. Is there anything missed out there?
<@U1F3CQ2HX>  - not sure if anyone responded.  error code 14 typically means the resource (endpoint is not available).  Looks like you are trying to add some new test case / functionality?
<@U1WUAQJVC>  - not sure I understand what you are trying to do?

<@U0PB67X4K> Yes, we are building a new usecase, we are running fabric network using docker-compose and running nodejs script to enroll registrar (admin) and other users. (All users including admin are configured in membersrvc.yaml).. we're getting this error when we try to enroll registrar (admin).
what does your compose yaml look like?
<@U0PB67X4K> Sorry i' cant send you now. Will send it to you on Sunday. But it has one membership and 3 VP nodes. Do we need to look at something specific in that.
the main thing to look at is to make sure the SDK is pointed at the correct URL for membership services
<@U0PB67X4K> yes, we did  actually by checking IP address & port of membership service.  We passed both a member service and VP url.
